# Terraform — Modules (Part 2)

## Modules

- Extract reusable components into `modules/`. Call from root or env dirs.
- Each module: `main.tf`, `variables.tf`, `outputs.tf`, `README.md`.
- **Pin module versions**: `source = "git::https://...?ref=v1.0"` or registry `version = "~> 1.0"`.

```hcl
# root main.tf
module "vpc" {
  source = "./modules/vpc"
  env    = var.env
  cidr   = var.vpc_cidr
}

module "rds" {
  source  = "./modules/rds"
  vpc_id  = module.vpc.id
  subnet_ids = module.vpc.private_subnet_ids
}
```

```hcl
# modules/vpc/main.tf
resource "aws_vpc" "main" {
  cidr_block           = var.cidr
  enable_dns_hostnames = true
  tags = {
    Name        = "${var.env}-vpc"
    Environment = var.env
    ManagedBy   = "Terraform"
  }
}
```

## Variables

- **Variables** for all configurable values. No hardcoded env-specific data in `.tf`.
- Use `variable` blocks with `type`, `description`, and `default` when sensible. Use `validation` blocks for constraints.
- Sensitive: `sensitive = true`; never log or output in plain text.
- Use `.tfvars` files for env-specific values; never commit secrets.
- Use `TF_VAR_*` env vars to pass values (e.g. `TF_VAR_db_password`); useful for CI and secrets.

```hcl
# variables.tf
variable "env" {
  type        = string
  description = "Environment (dev, staging, prod)"
}

variable "db_password" {
  type      = string
  sensitive = true
}

variable "region" {
  type        = string
  description = "AWS region"
  default     = "us-east-1"
  validation {
    condition     = can(regex("^[a-z]{2}-[a-z]+-[0-9]+$", var.region))
    error_message = "Region must be valid AWS region format."
  }
}

variable "project" {
  type        = string
  description = "Project name for tagging"
}

variable "instance_type" {
  type    = string
  default = "t3.micro"
}

variable "vpc_cidr" {
  type        = string
  description = "VPC CIDR block"
  default     = "10.0.0.0/16"
}

variable "enable_alerts" {
  type    = bool
  default = false
}

variable "allowed_ports" {
  type    = list(number)
  default = [80, 443]
}

variable "cidr" {
  type    = string
  default = "0.0.0.0/0"
}

variable "extra_volumes" {
  type    = list(any)
  default = []
}
```

## Outputs

- **Outputs** for values needed by other modules or scripts. Document each output.
- Never output sensitive values; use `sensitive = true` if unavoidable.
- Use `terraform plan -var-file=prod.tfvars` for env-specific plans.

```hcl
# outputs.tf
output "vpc_id" {
  value       = aws_vpc.main.id
  description = "VPC ID for other modules"
}

output "db_endpoint" {
  value       = aws_db_instance.main.endpoint
  description = "DB endpoint"
  sensitive   = true
}
```
